text: National Highway 753H, commonly referred to as NH 753H is a national highway in India. It is a secondary route of National Highway 53. NH-753H runs in the state of Maharashtra in India. == Route == NH753H connects Sillod, Bhokardan, Hasnabad, Rajur, Bawnepangri, Jalna, Ambad and Wadigodri in the state of Maharashtra. == Junctions == : Terminal near Sillod. : Terminal near Wadigodri. == See also == * List of National Highways in India * List of National Highways in India by state == References == == External links == * NH 753H on OpenStreetMap Category:National highways in India Category:National Highways in Maharashtra
